    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-02-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-02-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="288"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d288">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">710.11/198½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chilean Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Suárez-Mujica</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="2" xml:id="d288fn1">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                            mutandis</hi>, to the Argentine and Brazilian Ambassadors.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 1, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: I am enclosing, for your
                    confidential examination, the draft of a proposed convention,<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d288fn2">Enclosure as in President Wilson’s letter of Jan. 29, 1915,
                            <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> copies of which are being sent also
                    to the Ambassadors of Argentine and Brazil.</p>
                <p>I would appreciate it very much if you would call at my house at six o’clock this
                    evening so that we may go over the language together before the proposed
                    convention is forwarded to your respective countries. I am requesting you to
                    call at the house instead of the Department in order to avoid publicity, if
                    possible.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
